1
00:00:11,030 --> 00:00:14,210
♫ When romance is too insignificant ♫

2
00:00:14,210 --> 00:00:21,630
♫ But I can't stop missing you, like a bad cold ♫

3
00:00:21,630 --> 00:00:28,330
♫ Drifting in a deserted island, where feelings have no reception ♫

4
00:00:28,330 --> 00:00:32,150
♫ Have you been well? ♫

5
00:00:32,150 --> 00:00:36,200
♫ Don't worry, I'll be fine ♫

6
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:39,510
♫ Don't worry, I can't fall asleep ♫

7
00:00:39,510 --> 00:00:46,790
♫ Don't worry, I can't get used to this lonely world ♫

8
00:00:46,790 --> 00:00:53,650
♫ Hitting the pause button, leaving your side ♫

9
00:00:53,650 --> 00:01:00,770
♫ Letting the memories migrate to that day of happiness ♫

10
00:01:00,770 --> 00:01:07,060
♫ I'm trying hard to smile as I say goodbye to you ♫

11
00:01:07,060 --> 00:01:12,820
♫ I recall and long for the happiness you want, I can make it happen ♫

12
00:01:12,820 --> 00:01:16,080
♫ Can't hold back the tears, leading to regret ♫

13
00:01:16,080 --> 00:01:22,080
♫ Losing you whom I love, heartbreak is inevitable ♫

14
00:01:22,080 --> 00:01:28,540
♫ I choose to bid farewell with a smile ♫

15
00:01:28,540 --> 00:01:31,680
[Lost Romance]

16
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:33,760
Stepchild, stepchild, stepchild! You're simply a stepchild in the world of cooking! (Implies he is unwanted)

17
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:37,420
Unless you don't want to eat dinner, get out of my kitchen until I'm done cooking.

18
00:01:37,420 --> 00:01:40,600
CEO, there's a problem with today's contract. It needs to be revised immediately.

19
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:42,230
Chuchu is already on her way with the contract.

20
00:01:42,230 --> 00:01:43,570
I'll go back to my room as long as you agree that

21
00:01:43,570 --> 00:01:45,930
from this day forward, I get to eat at the dining table too.

22
00:01:45,930 --> 00:01:48,620
If you have a portion to eat, then so do I.

23
00:01:48,620 --> 00:01:50,140
Boss, are you okay?

24
00:01:50,140 --> 00:01:52,380
Did something happen to you when you were little?

25
00:01:52,380 --> 00:01:54,260
It's dark. It's slanted.

26
00:01:54,260 --> 00:01:56,550
Go to sleep! Sleep!

27
00:01:56,550 --> 00:01:58,150
Xiao'en, you'll stay here, right?

28
00:01:58,150 --> 00:02:00,110
You're not allowed to sneak away when I'm asleep.

29
00:02:00,110 --> 00:02:02,110
I'll sleep here.

30
00:02:02,110 --> 00:02:04,650
I promise I won't go anywhere.

31
00:02:04,650 --> 00:02:07,390
Even if I sleepwalk, I won't leave.

32
00:02:07,390 --> 00:02:10,120
The CEO's itinerary today is to inspect and approve all of the resort's

33
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:13,510
daytime and nighttime facilities and service plans.

34
00:02:13,510 --> 00:02:18,410
If he's satisfied, we will begin contract negotiations tomorrow.

35
00:02:18,410 --> 00:02:22,140
Tianxing once said that the employees are the company's most valuable asset.

36
00:02:22,140 --> 00:02:25,340
I fully understand everyone's request. I will pass the word on to the chairwoman.

37
00:02:25,340 --> 00:02:27,960
We absolutely won't treat you poorly.

38
00:02:33,750 --> 00:02:40,930
[Lost Romance]

39
00:02:40,930 --> 00:02:43,890
[Chapter Six]

40
00:02:43,890 --> 00:02:46,350
All of you,

41
00:02:46,350 --> 00:02:48,370
if you are willing to write a letter of repentance

42
00:02:48,370 --> 00:02:51,370
and admit that striking was a mistake that you won't make again in the future,

43
00:02:51,370 --> 00:02:54,030
please stand up and return to the office with me.

44
00:02:54,030 --> 00:02:58,610
We will forget that anything happened today.

45
00:02:59,460 --> 00:03:03,940
Tomorrow, everyone will continue to work hard together.

46
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:08,120
[On Strike]

47
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:11,920
[Stop suppressing us, negotiate with us immediately]
[Unethical company, wrongful layoffs]

48
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:20,310
Wow.

49
00:03:20,310 --> 00:03:22,700
That's so great.

50
00:03:22,700 --> 00:03:24,920
You guys have such a backbone.

51
00:03:24,920 --> 00:03:28,120
It's worth my applause for you.

52
00:03:31,190 --> 00:03:36,550
Qiaozhi, take down all of the strikers' names.

53
00:03:37,510 --> 00:03:39,620
All these people...

54
00:03:41,040 --> 00:03:44,190
Tianliang Group doesn't want them.

55
00:03:44,870 --> 00:03:47,960
- Let's start recruiting new people tomorrow.
- Yes.

56
00:03:49,050 --> 00:03:50,400
How could this happen?

57
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:52,680
- CHRO He, what do we do now?
- CHRO, go!

58
00:03:52,680 --> 00:03:55,160
- CHRO He.
- But...

59
00:03:56,170 --> 00:03:58,240
Sis.

60
00:03:58,240 --> 00:04:00,890
Chairwoman.

61
00:04:00,890 --> 00:04:03,390
Can you listen to me?

62
00:04:03,390 --> 00:04:06,190
Chairwoman?

63
00:04:06,190 --> 00:04:08,480
Sure sounds nice.

64
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:10,650
Are you angry with me right now?

65
00:04:10,650 --> 00:04:12,560
I also want to help the company resolve this problem.

66
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:15,020
Problem?

67
00:04:15,020 --> 00:04:18,650
Are you trying to tell them that I am the company's problem?

68
00:04:18,650 --> 00:04:21,950
Do you think I'd do that to you? We are family!

69
00:04:21,950 --> 00:04:24,500
When you tried to garner popular support behind my back,

70
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:26,950
did you think about me, your family?

71
00:04:26,950 --> 00:04:31,820
You know everyone's comparing me to He Tianxing and contradicting me,

72
00:04:31,820 --> 00:04:33,880
does this mean you are on his side?

73
00:04:33,880 --> 00:04:36,970
Goodness, aren't you getting a little off topic here?

74
00:04:38,750 --> 00:04:40,980
I know you hate He Tianxing,

75
00:04:40,980 --> 00:04:45,970
but you can't deny that most of our employees approve of him more.

76
00:04:46,670 --> 00:04:49,200
Right now, you insist on obliterating all of his contributions,

77
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:52,820
and then you take the opposing side from your employees. What good does this do you?

78
00:04:52,820 --> 00:04:55,230
- Even if—
- Also...

79
00:04:55,230 --> 00:04:59,580
We've never handled a strike before, but we at least know how to copy someone, right?

80
00:04:59,580 --> 00:05:02,790
How come He Tianxing can do it, but we can't?

81
00:05:08,620 --> 00:05:11,100
[Stop suppressing us, negotiate with us immediately]
[Unethical company, wrongful layoffs]

82
00:05:12,470 --> 00:05:14,090
Uncle Hu.

83
00:05:14,090 --> 00:05:16,040
Chairwoman.

84
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:19,630
I know about everything happening outside.

85
00:05:19,630 --> 00:05:21,700
You did a good job. A rare sight.

86
00:05:21,700 --> 00:05:23,530
You've grown up.

87
00:05:24,260 --> 00:05:28,880
But your work is not meticulous enough, not slick enough.

88
00:05:28,880 --> 00:05:33,010
You shouldn't have given out lunch boxes in your own name and negotiated with them.

89
00:05:33,010 --> 00:05:34,900
I'm not negotiating with them. I'm just trying to understand—

90
00:05:34,900 --> 00:05:39,520
No matter what, you should not take initiative in front of Chairwoman,

91
00:05:40,430 --> 00:05:43,310
especially since you have differing opinions.

92
00:05:43,310 --> 00:05:45,910
Think about what the employees on strike will think.

93
00:05:45,910 --> 00:05:49,370
They'll think that the CHRO is willing to talk with them,

94
00:05:49,370 --> 00:05:54,700
but our chairwoman doesn't even want to listen.

95
00:05:54,700 --> 00:06:02,040
Doesn't that indicate incapability, arrogance, and no empathy?

96
00:06:07,810 --> 00:06:10,000
It's okay, Uncle Hu.

97
00:06:10,730 --> 00:06:15,200
As the chairwoman, the decisions I make will never change.

98
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:18,010
- Sis, but—
- That's how it will be.

99
00:06:18,010 --> 00:06:19,950
Sis.

100
00:06:21,710 --> 00:06:23,940
Sis!

101
00:07:13,390 --> 00:07:17,150
The unique geographical location and soil quality of this place

102
00:07:17,150 --> 00:07:19,800
has resulted in the unique flavour of this coffee.

103
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:21,730
The bitterness is very subtle.

104
00:07:21,730 --> 00:07:24,280
The taste is smooth and sweet.

105
00:07:33,510 --> 00:07:36,480
The taste is quite strong and uniform.

106
00:07:36,480 --> 00:07:39,190
It really does have a special flavor.

107
00:07:39,190 --> 00:07:43,280
Local characteristics are well-integrated into the resort.

108
00:07:43,280 --> 00:07:47,610
This will be helpful in getting our foot in the door for the international tourism market.

109
00:07:50,790 --> 00:07:53,390
This is the contract for our collaboration.

110
00:07:53,390 --> 00:07:56,760
Although Royal Group's name will be used here in the future,

111
00:07:56,760 --> 00:07:59,950
as I keep emphasizing,

112
00:07:59,950 --> 00:08:03,760
Royal Group does not build cookie-cutter hotels.

113
00:08:03,760 --> 00:08:09,210
Please remember that everything that sets you apart from others is what I want.

114
00:08:09,840 --> 00:08:12,970
The contract has already been adjusted according to what we talked about earlier.

115
00:08:12,970 --> 00:08:15,210
- Please check.
- Okay.

116
00:08:15,210 --> 00:08:19,910
I'll sign the contract first thing tomorrow morning so that you can take it with you.

117
00:08:27,220 --> 00:08:30,080
I... I want to check in.

118
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:32,220
Okay. Do you have a reservation?

119
00:08:32,220 --> 00:08:33,690
No.

120
00:08:33,690 --> 00:08:35,330
I'll get you a glass of water.

121
00:08:35,330 --> 00:08:37,190
Thank you.

122
00:08:40,560 --> 00:08:42,970
Here you go.

123
00:08:48,680 --> 00:08:51,550
I'm sorry, but we only have one room left unbooked for today.

124
00:08:51,550 --> 00:08:54,140
It's a deluxe mountain view suite. You get your own hot spring.

125
00:08:54,140 --> 00:08:57,780
Dinner and breakfast is included, and you get one ticket to the spa.

126
00:08:57,780 --> 00:08:59,240
Perfect. I'll take that one.

127
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:02,140
Okay. The price for one person is NT$50,000 (~US$1,700).

128
00:09:02,140 --> 00:09:04,490
Are you paying by card?

129
00:09:06,990 --> 00:09:11,570
Excuse me. You said how many zeroes after the five?

130
00:09:11,570 --> 00:09:13,960
Four.

131
00:09:14,590 --> 00:09:19,950
Miss, if I don't eat anything and don't use the spa or the hot spring,

132
00:09:19,950 --> 00:09:22,040
can it be cheaper? A zero less?

133
00:09:22,040 --> 00:09:24,950
Mr. Situ, let's go inside.

134
00:09:26,160 --> 00:09:28,240
Miss, you dropped your pen. I'll get it for you.

135
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:30,620
Our work is done today.

136
00:09:30,620 --> 00:09:32,340
What do you think?

137
00:09:32,340 --> 00:09:37,190
Do you want to try the hot spring, spa, or hydrotherapy?

138
00:09:37,190 --> 00:09:39,860
I heard the dinner is quite a treat.

139
00:09:39,860 --> 00:09:42,140
Can we do it all?

140
00:09:42,140 --> 00:09:43,930
Of course.

141
00:09:50,590 --> 00:09:53,720
Swipe all you want for the deluxe mountain view suite.

142
00:09:53,720 --> 00:09:56,050
Okay.

143
00:09:57,180 --> 00:10:00,030
CEO Situ, this is your room card.

144
00:10:00,030 --> 00:10:02,800
Miss Chuchu, this is your room card. Your room is over there.

145
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:05,640
Then I'll let you both rest.

146
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:17,010
Get some rest first.

147
00:10:32,590 --> 00:10:34,980
CEO, is there anything you need to brief me on?

148
00:10:34,980 --> 00:10:37,990
The dinner reservation is at 7:30 PM.

149
00:10:47,030 --> 00:10:50,230
Miss, your room is not on this floor.

150
00:10:50,230 --> 00:10:52,300
I spent so much money. I just want to look around.

151
00:10:52,300 --> 00:10:56,690
But this whole floor is booked.

152
00:10:56,690 --> 00:10:59,150
I won't go in the rooms.

153
00:11:00,090 --> 00:11:02,360
Looking around the hallways is also very interesting.

154
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:05,370
Look, being alone in happiness is better than sharing my happiness.

155
00:11:05,370 --> 00:11:09,750
Over a thousand hills, no bird is in flight. I am an old man in a straw hat on a lone boat. (Reciting poetry)

156
00:11:09,750 --> 00:11:12,510
Who's in which room?

157
00:11:15,970 --> 00:11:18,000
Miss!

158
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:19,660
Don't worry about me. You can get back to work.

159
00:11:19,660 --> 00:11:23,330
No, but you'll disturb the other guests—

160
00:11:23,330 --> 00:11:28,640
If you don't make a sound and I don't make a sound, then no one will be disturbed. Okay?

161
00:11:30,320 --> 00:11:32,660
No, but—

162
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:36,660
Miss, please do me a favor.

163
00:11:36,660 --> 00:11:39,390
You're making this hard for me.

164
00:11:51,050 --> 00:11:52,990
What's wrong?

165
00:11:53,860 --> 00:11:55,660
CEO.

166
00:11:57,410 --> 00:12:02,490
I slipped in the bathroom and broke the mirror.

167
00:12:02,490 --> 00:12:04,200
It's alright. Let me look.

168
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:06,980
I'm bleeding.

169
00:12:08,570 --> 00:12:11,190
Hey, go help!

170
00:12:11,190 --> 00:12:12,930
Hurry!

171
00:12:14,620 --> 00:12:19,230
I absolutely won't give you guys the chance to perform the finger-sucking scene!

172
00:12:19,230 --> 00:12:22,720
Her room's mirror broke, and she hurt her hand.

173
00:12:22,720 --> 00:12:26,740
I'll bring the first aid kit immediately and have someone come clean up the room.

174
00:12:26,740 --> 00:12:29,790
Can you just get a new room for her?

175
00:12:29,790 --> 00:12:33,940
I'm sorry. The last room was just booked.

176
00:12:33,940 --> 00:12:36,340
We really don't have any more.

177
00:12:40,790 --> 00:12:43,940
It'll hurt a bit. Try to hold it in.

178
00:12:52,530 --> 00:12:54,230
Here.

179
00:13:18,590 --> 00:13:22,760
CEO Situ, the deluxe mountain view suite at the penthouse is ready.

180
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:24,600
Okay, I got it.

181
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:26,890
Didn't you say the hotel was completely booked?

182
00:13:26,890 --> 00:13:32,400
Well, actually... one woman who booked had something come up and decided to cancel.

183
00:13:33,910 --> 00:13:37,730
CEO, I can just stay here.

184
00:13:37,730 --> 00:13:40,180
We are here to work.

185
00:13:40,180 --> 00:13:43,020
Alright, I'm fine either way.

186
00:13:52,290 --> 00:13:54,290
My room is farther from here.

187
00:13:54,290 --> 00:13:57,160
Call me if anything happens, okay?

188
00:13:57,160 --> 00:13:59,010
Okay.

189
00:14:04,950 --> 00:14:07,670
I should have brought a tent.

190
00:14:15,630 --> 00:14:17,960
Tonight is the turning point in the plot.

191
00:14:17,960 --> 00:14:20,460
The author will use any method beyond reason

192
00:14:20,460 --> 00:14:24,290
to trap the main characters in the same room overnight.

193
00:14:26,460 --> 00:14:31,090
If that's the case, what's the use of sacrificing my own room?

194
00:14:31,090 --> 00:14:33,000
In any case, if they get drunk, they'll get in the wrong bed.

195
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:34,740
If there's an earthquake, they will cuddle.

196
00:14:34,740 --> 00:14:36,290
If one goes to the other's room to talk about work at night,

197
00:14:36,290 --> 00:14:38,700
the lock will definitely break and they'll be trapped.

198
00:14:38,700 --> 00:14:44,480
But in this world, where am I, the only person who can split them up?

199
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:48,660
I am everywhere!

200
00:14:48,660 --> 00:14:51,260
Just not in this resort.

201
00:14:52,530 --> 00:14:55,930
The thousands of romance novels I've read are all for nothing.

202
00:14:59,540 --> 00:15:04,190
I'm already frustrated enough, yet you bugs are still here making all this noise.

203
00:15:15,910 --> 00:15:17,440
- Miss!
- I'm looking for someone!

204
00:15:17,440 --> 00:15:20,580
You can't go in if you're not staying here, Miss!

205
00:15:22,280 --> 00:15:25,690
You can't go in if you didn't reserve a room, Miss!

206
00:15:27,990 --> 00:15:32,000
If you keep doing this, I'll call the cops. Miss!

207
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:38,940
Miss! Don't be like this!

208
00:15:41,260 --> 00:15:43,550
Give me a bit more time!

209
00:15:43,550 --> 00:15:46,000
You... can't!

210
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:49,260
You can't enter!

211
00:15:49,260 --> 00:15:51,430
I know.

212
00:15:52,050 --> 00:15:54,740
[Sauna (Men)]

213
00:15:56,410 --> 00:15:58,400
Miss!

214
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:02,550
You can't come in here. I will call the cops!

215
00:16:02,550 --> 00:16:04,950
I found the person I was looking for!

216
00:16:06,680 --> 00:16:09,590
Miss! Miss!

217
00:16:09,590 --> 00:16:12,770
Supreme Master Qingfeng, I'm with you, right?

218
00:16:42,040 --> 00:16:43,950
Use this.

219
00:16:45,930 --> 00:16:47,630
Didn't you say you weren't coming?

220
00:16:47,630 --> 00:16:52,970
You said something along the lines of "Timing's not important. We'll see each other next time."

221
00:16:54,500 --> 00:16:56,950
That is what I think.

222
00:17:00,300 --> 00:17:04,570
So did a criminal barge into your house and force you to come to the hot springs at gunpoint?

223
00:17:05,510 --> 00:17:07,600
No.

224
00:17:09,010 --> 00:17:11,550
I really didn't plan on coming.

225
00:17:11,550 --> 00:17:13,660
Aoran is a very good friend of mine.

226
00:17:13,660 --> 00:17:15,830
I don't want to sabotage him.

227
00:17:16,740 --> 00:17:20,440
But I don't know why...

228
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:23,990
When I was driving to work in the morning...

229
00:17:24,700 --> 00:17:28,410
I thought about when I drove Chuchu back to the company that night...

230
00:17:57,230 --> 00:17:59,570
Suddenly, you felt happy from the bottom of your heart.

231
00:17:59,570 --> 00:18:03,430
When you came back to your senses, you realized you were already on your way to the resort.

232
00:18:03,430 --> 00:18:04,930
Right?

233
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:07,850
How did you know?

234
00:18:07,850 --> 00:18:11,190
Because... this is love.

235
00:18:11,190 --> 00:18:13,230
Love doesn't have any reason.

236
00:18:16,380 --> 00:18:20,010
I also think there are no reasons behind my actions.

237
00:18:20,010 --> 00:18:23,380
I must have come here with the thought

238
00:18:23,380 --> 00:18:26,550
that no matter what happens between Aoran and Chuchu,

239
00:18:26,550 --> 00:18:29,420
I want to see it for myself.

240
00:18:30,560 --> 00:18:33,410
Then maybe I can give up.

241
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:41,350
It's useless for a kind guy like you to come here.

242
00:18:41,350 --> 00:18:43,640
You're not destructive at all.

243
00:18:43,640 --> 00:18:49,090
You can only watch helplessly and silently give them your blessings as they confirm each other's feelings.

244
00:18:49,870 --> 00:18:52,220
I'm not that great.

245
00:18:52,930 --> 00:18:55,390
You still don't understand yourself well enough.

246
00:18:56,970 --> 00:19:01,090
What about you? Why are you here?

247
00:19:01,090 --> 00:19:03,020
I'm here to change

248
00:19:03,930 --> 00:19:06,550
(His) plans for me.

249
00:19:10,030 --> 00:19:15,020
So you think destiny can be changed?

250
00:19:15,540 --> 00:19:19,950
Of course! As long as we help each other.

251
00:19:21,040 --> 00:19:25,050
Didn't you say I'm destined to silently give them my blessings?

252
00:19:26,030 --> 00:19:30,250
Destiny is destiny, but we can still fight for what we want.

253
00:19:38,950 --> 00:19:40,490
Feel what's in your heart.

254
00:19:40,490 --> 00:19:44,990
Whomever you want to push forward for, you will fight for her.

255
00:19:47,350 --> 00:19:50,820
You thought about Chuchu, so you came here at the turn of your steering wheel.

256
00:19:50,820 --> 00:19:54,470
I thought about the overbearing CEO, so I moved my feet and came here.

257
00:19:54,470 --> 00:19:56,270
Right?

258
00:20:24,830 --> 00:20:26,410
What's wrong?

259
00:20:26,410 --> 00:20:29,920
Sorry, I'm just an assistant.

260
00:20:29,920 --> 00:20:32,740
I should have let you eat first.

261
00:20:37,490 --> 00:20:39,880
From this day forward, I want to eat at the dining table too.

262
00:20:39,880 --> 00:20:42,940
If you have a portion to eat, then so do I.

263
00:20:45,100 --> 00:20:48,240
It's alright. Don't pay attention to that.

264
00:20:48,240 --> 00:20:50,700
CEO, you're so kind!

265
00:21:08,090 --> 00:21:09,900
Immature.

266
00:21:12,480 --> 00:21:17,770
Wow, I didn't think duck and peach would go so well together.

267
00:21:26,670 --> 00:21:29,130
Don't look.

268
00:21:29,130 --> 00:21:33,080
I'm not cute when I eat.

269
00:21:35,040 --> 00:21:37,240
It's this taste!

270
00:21:38,420 --> 00:21:41,390
Don't worry, you look better than someone else.

271
00:21:45,390 --> 00:21:49,600
There's somewhere I want to go to later.

272
00:21:49,600 --> 00:21:52,000
Can you accompany me?

273
00:21:59,300 --> 00:22:01,200
What's going on here?

274
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:04,280
Miss said you two are about to retire for the night and asked me to turn down the bed.

275
00:22:04,280 --> 00:22:06,580
Is that not right?

276
00:22:06,580 --> 00:22:09,410
Right! You're so right!

277
00:22:09,410 --> 00:22:11,290
Your service is amazing.

278
00:22:11,290 --> 00:22:14,330
When I check out, I will give you a five-star review.

279
00:22:14,330 --> 00:22:16,030
I'll tell your boss to give you a raise.

280
00:22:16,030 --> 00:22:20,000
Thank you. I hope you two have a great night.

281
00:22:27,510 --> 00:22:28,970
Why are you looking at me like that?

282
00:22:28,970 --> 00:22:32,780
Sometimes I really don't know if you are a genius or just an idiot.

283
00:22:32,780 --> 00:22:36,220
You stopped Chuchu and Aoran from spending the night in the same room,

284
00:22:36,220 --> 00:22:39,650
but why didn't you stop us from sharing a bed?

285
00:22:39,650 --> 00:22:44,010
If I stopped this, I'd be out there as mosquito food instead!

286
00:22:49,520 --> 00:22:51,330
Just think of this as military bunks.

287
00:22:51,330 --> 00:22:53,560
Two soldiers' camaraderie.

288
00:22:53,560 --> 00:22:56,040
Comrades helping one another out in the face of calamity.

289
00:22:56,040 --> 00:22:59,340
Do you really have no sense of danger?

290
00:22:59,340 --> 00:23:02,770
It's because I have such a strong sense of danger that I'm scared to take even a step away from the battlefield.

291
00:23:02,770 --> 00:23:07,650
You must know, the main characters' relationship development happens in minutes.

292
00:23:07,650 --> 00:23:10,710
Plus, I finally got into the resort.

293
00:23:10,710 --> 00:23:12,600
I'm absolutely not leaving!

294
00:23:13,300 --> 00:23:16,250
Fine. Why don't I leave then?

295
00:23:16,250 --> 00:23:18,590
I'll find another place to stay.

296
00:23:20,430 --> 00:23:22,580
Oh no, you shouldn't.

297
00:23:30,160 --> 00:23:31,840
That's not right.

298
00:23:31,840 --> 00:23:34,430
Why am I the one who has to leave?

299
00:23:34,430 --> 00:23:35,760
Hey, I booked this room.

300
00:23:35,760 --> 00:23:37,630
Look!

301
00:24:14,180 --> 00:24:16,060
How much farther?

302
00:24:16,060 --> 00:24:21,170
The receptionist said there's a small stream in around twenty meters.

303
00:24:21,170 --> 00:24:24,070
That's where all the fireflies are!

304
00:24:32,050 --> 00:24:33,930
Do you want to see them that badly?

305
00:24:35,050 --> 00:24:39,680
I heard the environment is very nice here, so there are a lot of fireflies.

306
00:24:39,680 --> 00:24:42,390
As if a milky way is flowing right under our feet!

307
00:24:42,390 --> 00:24:44,700
It must be beautiful!

308
00:24:55,960 --> 00:25:00,000
Hey, hey!

309
00:25:01,610 --> 00:25:03,770
Your bro Aoran is afraid of the dark.

310
00:25:03,770 --> 00:25:06,010
His little hands are trembling already.

311
00:25:06,010 --> 00:25:09,260
He's acting all tough in order to get the girl.

312
00:25:09,260 --> 00:25:11,530
You don't know what he experienced in the past.

313
00:25:11,530 --> 00:25:15,150
Don't make sarcastic remarks like this.

314
00:25:35,310 --> 00:25:37,900
CEO, do you hear it?

315
00:25:37,900 --> 00:25:40,490
- Hear what?
- The sound of water.

316
00:25:40,490 --> 00:25:43,270
It must be around here somewhere.

317
00:25:43,270 --> 00:25:45,220
Where are you going?

318
00:25:45,220 --> 00:25:47,260
To look for fireflies.

319
00:25:47,260 --> 00:25:50,390
I heard they hide under the leaves.

320
00:26:04,190 --> 00:26:06,180
Have you found them?

321
00:26:10,150 --> 00:26:16,230
No. I think maybe our light's too bright, so they're hiding.

322
00:26:16,230 --> 00:26:19,000
Can we turn off the light?

323
00:26:24,720 --> 00:26:26,930
Can't we?

324
00:26:29,230 --> 00:26:32,000
Okay, I'll turn it off.

325
00:28:13,970 --> 00:28:16,700
Love is so powerful.

326
00:28:16,700 --> 00:28:19,500
All the lights at home have to be on,

327
00:28:19,500 --> 00:28:25,010
but now he can turn off the lights in the woods to see fireflies with his darling.

328
00:28:29,970 --> 00:28:31,920
CEO, look.

329
00:28:31,920 --> 00:28:33,620
Over there!

330
00:28:35,400 --> 00:28:38,990
It's great. So beautiful.

331
00:28:52,950 --> 00:28:53,930
Why did you suddenly—

332
00:28:53,930 --> 00:28:57,130
It's too late. Let's go back.

333
00:29:35,140 --> 00:29:36,960
Are you okay?

334
00:29:39,440 --> 00:29:41,160
I'm fine.

335
00:29:42,720 --> 00:29:45,970
There are a lot of mosquitoes out here. Let's get going.

336
00:29:49,600 --> 00:29:53,430
I wondered if we'd be able to save money on buying light bulbs if we collected enough fireflies.

337
00:29:53,430 --> 00:29:57,820
But all the fireflies I caught ended up dead in the bag the next day.

338
00:29:57,820 --> 00:30:01,090
How could I be so stupid? Fireflies are very fragile.

339
00:30:01,090 --> 00:30:03,820
And they are very pitiful like this.

340
00:30:03,820 --> 00:30:06,480
I won't do it again.

341
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:10,730
I really need to think about how next time, I can—

342
00:30:10,730 --> 00:30:12,350
Careful.

343
00:30:13,730 --> 00:30:15,900
How about I carry the light?

344
00:30:15,900 --> 00:30:20,030
It's okay. You walk behind me. It's safer that way.

345
00:30:26,970 --> 00:30:29,830
You allow your subordinates to blatantly bully their coworkers at work?

346
00:30:29,830 --> 00:30:33,030
You're treating me as a chauffeur?
(He refers to himself as "shaoye" which means "young master")

347
00:30:35,110 --> 00:30:37,020
Go back to your room.

348
00:30:38,720 --> 00:30:40,480
Let's go.

349
00:30:48,340 --> 00:30:51,140
Let's go! Or else we won't be able to keep up.

350
00:30:52,900 --> 00:30:55,340
What's the point of chasing?

351
00:30:55,340 --> 00:30:58,130
True love can give him courage.

352
00:30:58,130 --> 00:31:00,170
What can I give him?

353
00:31:00,170 --> 00:31:02,140
What do you want to give him?

354
00:31:02,140 --> 00:31:05,300
Didn't we come to ruin their relationship?

355
00:31:05,300 --> 00:31:08,000
Why are you worrying about Aoran instead?

356
00:31:23,670 --> 00:31:24,940
There's some over there too!

357
00:31:24,940 --> 00:31:27,290
CEO, I'll go catch some for you to see.

358
00:31:27,290 --> 00:31:29,190
No, it's okay!

359
00:31:41,430 --> 00:31:43,260
Did you hear that?

360
00:31:44,140 --> 00:31:45,950
It seems like...

361
00:31:48,460 --> 00:31:50,320
Help!

362
00:31:51,990 --> 00:31:54,980
Help me! Help!

363
00:31:57,710 --> 00:32:01,750
Help! Help!

364
00:32:01,750 --> 00:32:04,260
- Help!
- Grab tight!

365
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:07,450
Help!

366
00:32:08,380 --> 00:32:10,450
Help!

367
00:32:25,560 --> 00:32:28,970
CEO! CEO!

368
00:32:30,310 --> 00:32:32,960
Aoran! Chuchu!

369
00:32:34,380 --> 00:32:36,240
What happened?

370
00:32:36,240 --> 00:32:38,060
Situ Aoran.

371
00:32:38,060 --> 00:32:41,480
Situ Aoran, wake up! Situ Aoran!

372
00:32:41,480 --> 00:32:42,880
Hurry and call an ambulance!

373
00:32:42,880 --> 00:32:46,410
♫ Lost to you ♫

374
00:32:46,410 --> 00:32:54,110
♫ I think of you until I can no longer breathe ♫

375
00:32:54,110 --> 00:32:57,410
♫ My last wish is to never regret ♫

376
00:32:57,410 --> 00:33:03,540
♫ Brave out the heartbreak to no longer be afraid of heartbreaks ♫

377
00:33:03,540 --> 00:33:10,030
♫ I choose to bid farewell with a smile ♫

378
00:33:11,580 --> 00:33:13,950
Help!

379
00:33:15,130 --> 00:33:18,000
Help me! Help!

380
00:33:20,870 --> 00:33:24,430
Help! Help!

381
00:33:24,950 --> 00:33:27,210
- Help!
-Grab tight!

382
00:33:28,200 --> 00:33:30,630
Help!

383
00:33:31,400 --> 00:33:33,960
Help!

384
00:33:48,660 --> 00:33:51,680
CEO! CEO!

385
00:33:52,920 --> 00:33:55,440
Aoran! Chuchu!

386
00:33:56,820 --> 00:33:58,910
What happened?

387
00:33:58,910 --> 00:34:00,600
Situ Aoran.

388
00:34:00,600 --> 00:34:04,570
Situ Aoran, wake up! Situ Aoran!

389
00:34:04,570 --> 00:34:06,990
Hurry and call an ambulance!

390
00:34:09,900 --> 00:34:11,700
Situ Aoran.

391
00:34:12,980 --> 00:34:16,050
Can you hear me? Situ Aoran.

392
00:34:16,050 --> 00:34:17,710
Situ Aoran!

393
00:34:17,710 --> 00:34:20,200
What did you say? Critical condition?

394
00:34:20,200 --> 00:34:24,080
The hospital doctors are currently trying to save him, but the situation is not optimistic.

395
00:34:27,110 --> 00:34:29,190
Where are you going?

396
00:34:29,190 --> 00:34:30,680
You can drive a motorcycle, right?

397
00:34:30,680 --> 00:34:33,150
- Can you take me somewhere?
- Yes, where?

398
00:34:33,150 --> 00:34:35,320
The hospital!

399
00:34:36,610 --> 00:34:38,910
Please come quickly!

400
00:34:40,240 --> 00:34:42,070
Situ Aoran.

401
00:34:42,070 --> 00:34:44,810
Situ Aoran, wake up! Situ Aoran!

402
00:34:44,810 --> 00:34:47,590
Situ Aoran, can you hear me?

403
00:34:47,590 --> 00:34:51,670
Situ Aoran. Situ Aoran!

404
00:35:14,340 --> 00:35:16,870
- Zheng Xiao'en!
- Just hold on a little longer! Just a little longer!

405
00:35:16,870 --> 00:35:19,990
The ambulance is already on the way!

406
00:35:27,110 --> 00:35:28,230
Mom.

407
00:35:28,230 --> 00:35:31,270
Mingli, your dad... he's...

408
00:35:40,360 --> 00:35:42,250
Hold it in place.

409
00:35:47,050 --> 00:35:48,670
- Dad!
- How could this happen?

410
00:35:48,670 --> 00:35:49,970
This is an emergency procedure.

411
00:35:49,970 --> 00:35:53,150
Family members of the patient, please wait outside.

412
00:35:55,250 --> 00:35:57,510
Mom, calm down.

413
00:35:59,970 --> 00:36:01,910
Prepare the electric shock.

414
00:36:03,060 --> 00:36:04,880
[Charging to 200 joules]

415
00:36:06,050 --> 00:36:07,710
Clear.

416
00:36:09,970 --> 00:36:11,810
Set it to 250.

417
00:36:11,810 --> 00:36:14,120
- Setting to 250.
- Clear.

418
00:36:14,120 --> 00:36:15,250
Everyone, stop!

419
00:36:15,250 --> 00:36:18,950
Can't you see that Zhaonan is suffering?

420
00:36:19,510 --> 00:36:21,440
Don't stop!

421
00:36:22,040 --> 00:36:25,590
Sis, look at Dad!

422
00:36:25,590 --> 00:36:28,700
How can you bear to treat him like this?

423
00:36:34,980 --> 00:36:39,460
No. I don't have the will.

424
00:36:40,270 --> 00:36:42,100
Dad can't die yet!

425
00:36:42,100 --> 00:36:44,120
He Mingli!

426
00:36:45,710 --> 00:36:47,760
I don't care what methods you use.

427
00:36:47,760 --> 00:36:50,210
My dad is not allowed to die!

428
00:36:52,310 --> 00:36:54,850
Do something!

429
00:36:55,710 --> 00:36:58,050
Put him onto the ECMO (life support).

430
00:37:03,350 --> 00:37:06,180
Doctor, is he okay?

431
00:37:06,870 --> 00:37:09,740
He had stopped breathing, but fortunately it was discovered early.

432
00:37:09,740 --> 00:37:11,390
He's fine now.

433
00:37:11,940 --> 00:37:13,910
Thank you, Doctor.

434
00:37:37,260 --> 00:37:38,770
Careful.

435
00:37:40,010 --> 00:37:41,580
It must hurt a lot.

436
00:37:42,130 --> 00:37:44,820
It'll take some more effort to walk now.

437
00:37:44,820 --> 00:37:46,930
You'll have to bear with it for a while.

438
00:37:46,930 --> 00:37:51,310
I'm fine. I'm just worried about CEO.

439
00:37:51,890 --> 00:37:57,210
If it weren't for me, he wouldn't have gotten hurt.

440
00:38:07,020 --> 00:38:10,260
It seems like he'll wake up soon. Hurry, everyone get into position!

441
00:38:11,070 --> 00:38:13,530
Hurry!

442
00:38:13,530 --> 00:38:16,410
After almost experiencing death,

443
00:38:16,410 --> 00:38:20,610
the first person he sees upon waking up should be the person that he longs for the most.

444
00:38:21,300 --> 00:38:23,230
Hurry and sit.

445
00:38:32,310 --> 00:38:36,440
But why are you here?

446
00:38:38,650 --> 00:38:41,470
I came to upset the boss.

447
00:38:41,470 --> 00:38:45,380
But now that he's become like this, I've suddenly become more compassionate.

448
00:38:46,460 --> 00:38:48,770
What are you saying?

449
00:38:51,090 --> 00:38:53,380
If you have some compassion for our CEO,

450
00:38:53,380 --> 00:38:55,540
you must not tell him that I was here.

451
00:38:55,540 --> 00:38:58,340
Otherwise, he'll definitely be really mad.

452
00:38:58,340 --> 00:39:02,550
Promise? Promise!

453
00:39:02,550 --> 00:39:05,240
I promise.

454
00:39:05,240 --> 00:39:08,220
Okay. Look at him, not me!

455
00:39:21,100 --> 00:39:23,460
You're awake.

456
00:39:25,080 --> 00:39:26,930
Are you okay?

457
00:39:29,080 --> 00:39:31,730
The person laying down is asking the sitting person if she's okay.

458
00:39:31,730 --> 00:39:35,430
Of course he's never worried about himself.

459
00:39:35,430 --> 00:39:39,000
He can only see the other person's tiny injury.

460
00:39:42,240 --> 00:39:44,200
You brought me to the hospital?

461
00:39:47,660 --> 00:39:49,460
Thank you.

462
00:39:49,460 --> 00:39:53,200
I didn't expect that you'd save me.

463
00:39:55,840 --> 00:40:00,080
I had thought that it would pass after I held on for a bit.

464
00:40:00,080 --> 00:40:02,480
It's all my fault.

465
00:40:03,270 --> 00:40:05,660
If I didn't try to be clever

466
00:40:05,660 --> 00:40:08,440
and insist that we see the fireflies,

467
00:40:08,440 --> 00:40:10,980
it wouldn't have turned out like this.

468
00:40:12,410 --> 00:40:14,240
You never expected this, right?

469
00:40:15,190 --> 00:40:18,980
A big man like me would be afraid of the dark.

470
00:40:19,470 --> 00:40:22,070
Why are you afraid of the dark?

471
00:40:27,610 --> 00:40:31,060
- When I was little, whenever I made a little mistake,
- Get inside!

472
00:40:31,060 --> 00:40:34,350
- my dad would lock me in the cupboard.
- Dad, open the door.

473
00:40:34,350 --> 00:40:40,130
- No matter how much I cried or pleaded, it was no use.
- Dad, open the door.

474
00:40:40,130 --> 00:40:43,240
Sometimes I would be shut in for a whole day.

475
00:40:43,240 --> 00:40:46,180
I wouldn't get any food or water.

476
00:40:47,570 --> 00:40:49,910
The cupboard was so dark.

477
00:40:49,910 --> 00:40:52,010
There wasn't even a little bit of light.

478
00:41:01,270 --> 00:41:05,120
One time, Dad came in with a candle.

479
00:41:05,120 --> 00:41:08,710
- Dad!
- I thought he knew I was afraid of the dark

480
00:41:08,710 --> 00:41:12,500
and wanted to give me a light, but that wasn't the case.

481
00:41:12,500 --> 00:41:16,740
Don't drip it on me.

482
00:41:16,740 --> 00:41:22,930
Dad, don't drip it on me.

483
00:41:31,490 --> 00:41:35,910
It's alright. It's all in the past.

484
00:41:35,910 --> 00:41:38,560
Didn't I grow up just fine?

485
00:41:45,690 --> 00:41:48,150
I think maybe the circuit breaker tripped.

486
00:41:48,150 --> 00:41:50,430
I was just going to say that you got lucky.

487
00:41:50,430 --> 00:41:53,290
I'm not just a cute housekeeper; I'm also a sweetheart electrician.

488
00:41:53,290 --> 00:41:55,460
As long as I'm here, everything can be fixed quickly.

489
00:41:55,460 --> 00:42:00,850
♫ Silently frozen like a statue ♫

490
00:42:00,850 --> 00:42:04,050
♫ The smile hollows out the shell ♫

491
00:42:04,050 --> 00:42:05,980
What?

492
00:42:08,350 --> 00:42:11,400
Did something happen to you when you were little?

493
00:42:11,400 --> 00:42:13,300
Were you kidnapped? Abused?

494
00:42:13,300 --> 00:42:15,680
Shut up!

495
00:42:15,680 --> 00:42:20,970
♫ Like a sugar-coated lie ♫

496
00:42:23,350 --> 00:42:28,030
Are you okay? Hey.

497
00:42:28,030 --> 00:42:31,370
♫ Let me accompany you in insomnia ♫

498
00:42:31,370 --> 00:42:34,940
Why couldn't they let him grow up happily?

499
00:42:36,930 --> 00:42:41,310
Does there have to be regrets and flaws?

500
00:42:41,310 --> 00:42:45,250
♫ How warm the sun is ♫

501
00:42:45,830 --> 00:42:48,830
He's just a fictitious character, not a real person.

502
00:42:48,830 --> 00:42:51,280
Why does it tug at my heartstrings?

503
00:42:51,280 --> 00:42:55,330
I've read more than 87 books with childhood trauma.

504
00:42:55,330 --> 00:42:57,200
If it's not a family suddenly becoming poor or both parents dying,

505
00:42:57,200 --> 00:42:59,600
it's picking up the wrong child or psychological abuse.

506
00:42:59,600 --> 00:43:04,130
They always write about those. So old-fashioned.

507
00:43:06,180 --> 00:43:08,380
Then why do you still cry?

508
00:43:09,690 --> 00:43:12,440
♫ No matter how hard the pain is ♫

509
00:43:12,440 --> 00:43:14,120
Yeah.

510
00:43:14,870 --> 00:43:17,180
Why do I still cry?

511
00:43:17,180 --> 00:43:20,460
♫ There will be no more parting ♫

512
00:43:20,460 --> 00:43:23,330
Is it because I can see him

513
00:43:24,880 --> 00:43:26,970
and touch him

514
00:43:30,010 --> 00:43:33,060
that all the fear he's experienced

515
00:43:34,920 --> 00:43:37,440
seems to have become real?

516
00:43:41,850 --> 00:43:44,300
